337 class Control
338 {
339 public:
340 Edu totalDur{};
341 Evpu totalWidth{};
342 Evpu minWidth{};
343 Evpu allotWidth{};
344
345 static const xml::XmlElementArray<Control>& xmlMappingArray();
346 };
347
348 // Populated only when the XML node includes a <control> element
349 std::shared_ptr<Control> control;
350
351 // Populated for standard beat entries (inci > 0)
352 Edu dur{};
353 Evpu pos{};
354 Evpu endPos{};
355 Evpu minPos{};
356
357 void integrityCheck(const std::shared_ptr<Base>& ptrToThis) override
358 {
359 OthersBase::integrityCheck(ptrToThis);
360 if (control && getInci() != 0) {
361 MUSX_INTEGRITY_ERROR("Beat chart for measure " + std::to_string(getCmper()) + " has a control instance in inci " + std::to_string(*getInci()));
362 }
363 if (getInci() == 0 && !control) {
364 control = std::make_shared<Control>();
365 MUSX_INTEGRITY_ERROR("Beat chart for measure " + std::to_string(getCmper()) + " is missing its control instance.");
366 }
367 }
368
369 constexpr static std::string_view XmlNodeName = "beatChart";
370 static const xml::XmlElementArray<BeatChartElement>& xmlMappingArray();
371};

519class FontDefinition : public OthersBase
520{
521 static constexpr uint32_t SYMBOL_CHARSET_MAC = 0xfff; // (4095)
522 static constexpr uint32_t SYMBOL_CHARSET_WIN = 2;
523
524public:
526 explicit FontDefinition(const DocumentWeakPtr& document, Cmper partId, ShareMode shareMode, Cmper cmper)
527 : OthersBase(document, partId, shareMode, cmper) {}
528
531 enum class CharacterSetBank
532 {
533 MacOS,
534 Windows
535 };
536
537 // Public properties corresponding to the XML structure
538 CharacterSetBank charsetBank{};
539 int charsetVal{};
544 int pitch{};
545 int family{};
546 std::string name;
547
561 bool calcIsSymbolFont() const
562 {
563 if (charsetBank == CharacterSetBank::MacOS && charsetVal == SYMBOL_CHARSET_MAC) {
564 return true;
565 }
566 if (charsetBank == CharacterSetBank::Windows && charsetVal == SYMBOL_CHARSET_WIN) {
567 return true;
568 }
569 return false;
570 }
571
572 constexpr static std::string_view XmlNodeName = "fontName";
573 static const xml::XmlElementArray<FontDefinition>& xmlMappingArray();
574};

587class Frame : public OthersBase
588{
589public:
591 explicit Frame(const DocumentWeakPtr& document, Cmper partId, ShareMode shareMode, Cmper cmper, Inci inci = 0)
592 : OthersBase(document, partId, shareMode, cmper, inci) {}
593
594 // Public properties corresponding to the XML structure
595 EntryNumber startEntry{};
596 EntryNumber endEntry{};
597 Edu startTime{};
598
601 void iterateRawEntries(std::function<bool(const MusxInstance<Entry>& entry)> iterator) const;
602
607 MusxInstanceList<Entry> getEntries() const;
608
609 void integrityCheck(const std::shared_ptr<Base>& ptrToThis) override
610 {
611 this->OthersBase::integrityCheck(ptrToThis);
612 if (startTime && (startEntry || endEntry)) {
613 MUSX_INTEGRITY_ERROR("Frame " + std::to_string(getCmper()) + " has non-zero startTime and non-zero startEntry or endEntry.");
614 }
615 if (!startTime && !startEntry) {
616 MUSX_INTEGRITY_ERROR("Frame " + std::to_string(getCmper()) + " has no start entry.");
617 }
618 if (!startTime && !endEntry) {
619 MUSX_INTEGRITY_ERROR("Frame " + std::to_string(getCmper()) + " has no end entry.");
620 }
621 }
622
623 constexpr static std::string_view XmlNodeName = "frameSpec";
624 static const xml::XmlElementArray<Frame>& xmlMappingArray();

683 class StringInfo
684 {
685 public:
686 int pitch{};
687 int nutOffset{};
689
690 static const xml::XmlElementArray<StringInfo>& xmlMappingArray();
691 };
692
693 int numFrets{};
694 int numStrings{};
695 std::string name;
696 std::vector<std::shared_ptr<StringInfo>> strings;
697 std::vector<int> fretSteps;
701 ClefIndex speedyClef{};
702
703 void integrityCheck(const std::shared_ptr<Base>& ptrToThis) override
704 {
705 this->OthersBase::integrityCheck(ptrToThis);
706 if (numStrings != strings.size()) {
707 MUSX_INTEGRITY_ERROR("Fret instrument " + std::to_string(getCmper()) + " specifies " + std::to_string(numStrings)
708 + " strings but only has " + std::to_string(strings.size()) + " StringInfo instances.");
709 }
710 if (!fretSteps.empty() && numFrets > fretSteps.size()) {
711 util::Logger::log(util::Logger::LogLevel::Info, "Fret instrument " + std::to_string(getCmper()) + " specifies " + std::to_string(numFrets)
712 + " frets but only has " + std::to_string(fretSteps.size()) + " diatonic fret steps specified.");
713 }
714 }
715
716 constexpr static std::string_view XmlNodeName = "fretInst";
717 static const xml::XmlElementArray<FretboardInstrument>& xmlMappingArray();
718};
